<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-167-964  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 167 964.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Executive  Wntr 1990 v3 n1 p45(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The multimedia home PC: a vision and its challenges. (Perspectiveson the Future)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Waks, David J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The multimedia home PC is a concept envisioned since 1985 thatcombines features of television sets, microcomputers and CD-ROMsto deliver entertainment, interaction and memory.andP;  The first suchsystems will use a modem and a telephone connection to provideaccess to the latest text and graphics; external pictures andsound will be received via cable television, satellites or fiberoptics.andP;  The systems will be used to enhance current software withpictures and sound, to create new forms of interactiveentertainment, to provide a new education medium and to receivecustomized data on a range of topics of interest to familymembers.andP;  The concept involves both consumer electronics andcomputers, two very different industries.andP;  How to get the twoindustries to work together to deliver systems such as themultimedia home PC is discussed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TelevisionMultimedia TechnologyNew TechniqueFuture TechnologiesHome EntertainmentMicrocomputersOutlookConsumer ElectronicsIndustry Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>